on.英释: used to say what part of someone or something is hit or touched

my.英释: of or belonging to the speaker or writer

be.英释: used to say that someone or something is the same as the subject of the sentence

it.英释: used to refer to a thing, animal, situation, idea etc that has already been mentioned or is already known about

me.英释: used by the person speaking or writing to refer to himself or herself

go.英释: to move in a particular way, or to do something as you are moving

or.英释: used between two words or phrases to show that either of two things is possible, or used before the last in a list of possibilities or choices

if.英释: used when talking about something that might happen or be true, or might have happened

in.英释: used with the name of a container, place, or area to say where someone or something is

at.英释: used to say exactly where something or someone is, or where something happens

of.英释: used to show what a part belongs to or comes from

he.英释: used to refer to a man, boy, or male animal that has already been mentioned or is already known about

do.英释: to perform an action or activity

oh.英释: used when you want to get someone’s attention or continue what you are saying

ox.英释: a bull whose sex organs have been removed, often used for working on farms
